A group under the auspices of Plateau Unity Forum for Biggs (PUFFSB) has donated interest and nomination forms to the All Progressives Congress(APC) governorship aspirant, Sunday Garba Biggs. Sunday Biggs, who is vying for the number one seat on the Plateau, hails from Mangu Local Government Area.   Emir of Biu ‘endorses’ lawmaker’s re-election bid     Idoma poised to produce Benue governor next year     350 benefit from Plateau Speaker’s empowerment   This was made known when the group presented the expression of interest/nomination forms to the former Permanent Secretary, Sunday Garba Biggs, at the National Union Teachers’ (NUT) Hall, Plateau State, with party stalwarts and stakeholders in attendance. The leader of Plateau Unity Forum for Sunday Biggs (PUFFSB), Jonathan Mancha said the group witnessed his leadership qualities, his overall acceptance of his candidature by the people, coupled with his vast experience; having served under three different past governors. This, it said, gave them the pointer for them to adopt Sunday Biggs as their anointed candidate. He described Sunday Biggs as a compassionate, loyal and sincere individual and so believes in his ability to govern Plateau State.